{"timestamp":"2026-06-19T05:29:36.056Z","type":"tool","initiativeId":"implement-directory-v2-compatibility","step":"IDLE","details":{"toolName":"task","args":{"description":"Evaluate compatibility work","prompt":"Read-only evaluation. Initiative: implement-directory-v2-compatibility.\n\nObjective: Make harness-mdocs contract-aware so it supports both flat-v1 projects and agents-workspace-style directory-v2 mdocs without clobbering lowercase wiki/index.md or directory initiative structure.\n\nCurrent plan:\n1. Add mdocs contract detection and explicit compatibility config overrides.\n2. Refactor initiative access behind an InitiativeStore adapter shared by status, lookup, search, dispatch, validation, archive, and index checks.\n3. Implement directory-v2 initiative adapter for folder/_status.md initiatives, _archive/, legacy flat-file coexistence, status aliases, and safe writes.\n4. Add index ownership policy so canonical lowercase wiki/index.md is external-owned and generated uppercase INDEX.md files are disabled unless explicitly configured.\n5. Update wiki store/list/search/validation to include root wiki pages and resolve category/id plus root references safely.\n6. Update graph validation for sources, source_initiatives, related_wiki, related_initiatives, lifecycle: stable, and complete/done aliases.\n7. Add optional Obsidian refresh hook detection without treating _obsidian/ as canonical data.\n8. Add directory-v2 fixture and regression tests proving no unwanted INDEX.md generation or wiki/index.md clobbering.\n\nGist compatibility request summary:\n- Current harness assumes flat initiative files directly under mdocs/initiatives named <slug>--<date>.md, status active|paused|done, wiki pages only category dirs, generated wiki/INDEX.md + category INDEX.md, plugin owns indices.\n- Target directory-v2: initiatives mostly mdocs/initiatives/<slug>/_status.md, statuses active|paused|complete|archived, archived under _archive/<slug>/, root wiki pages first-class, lowercase wiki/index.md canonical and external-owned, no generated uppercase or category INDEX.md, optional _obsidian visibility layer.\n- Must support flat-v1 too; do not migrate directory-v2 repos to flat.\n\nTask: inspect code structure and tests enough to brainstorm/evaluate implementation. Do NOT edit files. Return concise evaluation:\n1. Current relevant files/modules and responsibilities.\n2. Dependency/call graph hotspots where flat assumptions live.\n3. Recommended implementation phases with risk level.\n4. Minimal first PR scope.\n5. Test strategy and likely test files to add/update.\n6. Open questions/blockers.\n\nVerification criteria: evaluation maps plan to concrete files and minimizes clobber risk.","subagent_type":"explore","task_id":"","command":"evaluate mdocs directory-v2 compatibility"}}}
